E.%20%26quot%3BWe%20owed%20them%20as%20much%20effort%20as%20possible%20to%20make%20this%20as%20painless%20as%20possible%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Newlin%20didn't%20know%20any%20other%20families%20who%20had%20tried%20a%20similar%20living%20arrangement%2C%20which%20has%20become%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bnesting.%26quot%3B%20While%20the%20idea%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnesting-divorce-helps-coparent-financially-responsible-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enesting%20after%20a%20breakup%20or%20divorce%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20work%20well%20for%20some%2C%20family%20and%20relationship%20experts%20who%20spoke%20with%20Business%20Insider%20caution%20that%20it%20can%20be%20difficult%20to%20pull%20off%20in%20practice%20because%20it%20requires%20a%20high%20level%20of%20trust%20and%20communication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20only%20works%20for%20a%20very%20slim%20margin%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Olivia%20Howell%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freshstartsregistry.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFresh%20Starts%20Registry%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20helps%20people%20navigate%20divorce%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226f36f12e-f2d2-4b1c-b364-e7f706c0a1ed%5C%22%3EIntentional%20planning%20is%20critical%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fcooperativecoparenting%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAurisha%20Smolarski%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20licensed%20family%20therapist%2C%20decided%20to%20get%20divorced%20quickly.%20She%20was%20concerned%20about%20the%20abruptness%20of%20the%20transition%20for%20her%20daughter%2C%20who%20was%206%20years%20old%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20her%20ex-husband%20tried%20nesting.%20Like%20Newlin%2C%20they%20also%20didn't%20know%20what%20it%20was%20called%20when%20they%20started%20the%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20regret%20doing%20it%20slowly%20for%20her%2C%20and%20I%20believe%20it%20set%20her%20up%20for%20success%20when%20we%20moved%20into%20the%20new%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20Smolarski%2C%20who%20is%20also%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aurishasmolarski.com%2Fbook%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECooperative%20Coparenting%20for%20Secure%20Kids%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20nesting%20%26quot%3Bjust%20didn't%20work%20for%20us%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20and%20her%20ex-husband%20were%20still%20arguing%2C%20and%20they%20eventually%20realized%20that%20their%20daughter%20could%20overhear.%20That%20made%20them%20very%20concerned%20and%20led%20to%20the%20realization%20that%20their%20new%20arrangement%2C%20designed%20to%20benefit%20her%20daughter%2C%20wasn't%20actually%20helping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20underscores%20a%20problem%20that%20Smolarski%20sees%20professionally%20with%20nesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOften%2C%20people%20will%20roll%20right%20into%20it%20with%20the%20old%20habits%20that%20may%20not%20work%2C%20or%20may%20never%20have%20worked%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20should%20exes%20consider%20where%20they%20stand%20with%20each%20other%2C%20but%20counselor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mindfulkindnesscounseling.com%2Fcounseling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBonnie%20Scott%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20said%20that%20parents%20need%20to%20coparent%20together%20really%20well%20in%20order%20to%20consider%20nesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20keep%20a%20really%20good%20coparenting%20relationship%20and%20try%20out%20nesting%2C%20it's%20worth%20a%20shot%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20the%20coparenting%20relationship%20would%20be%20better%20with%20the%20traditional%20setup%2C%20that's%20really%20the%20more%20important%20factor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParents%20should%20also%20consider%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdivorce-share-custody-kids-parenting-plan-time-regret-decision-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecustody%20split%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Nesting%20might%20work%20well%20for%20a%2050%2F50%20split%2C%20where%20each%20adult%20feels%20equally%20invested%20in%20the%20family%20home%2C%20but%20less%20well%20if%20one%20parent%20only%20has%20the%20kids%20every%20other%20weekend%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22400d525b-bc15-4b9f-9191-90153646b369%5C%22%3ENesters%20need%20to%20work%20together%20to%20handle%20logistics%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENewlin%20credits%20careful%20planning%20for%20making%20her%20arrangement%20work%20long-term.%20She%20said%20she%20and%20her%20ex%20spent%20nine%20months%20and%20many%20therapy%20sessions%20(apart%20and%20together)%20before%20their%20divorce%2C%20hashing%20out%20the%20details%20before%20they%20moved%20forward%20with%20nesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20really%20thought%20it%20out%20and%20planned%20it%20carefully%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20beginning%2C%20that%20included%20formal%20weekly%20check-ins%20over%20Zoom%2C%20where%20they%20discussed%20everything%20from%20upcoming%20school%20events%20to%20whose%20turn%20it%20was%20to%20take%20out%20the%20trash.%20These%20days%2C%20it's%20more%20fluid%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20only%20check%20in%20when%20we%20see%20big%20issues%20that%20we%20don't%20already%20have%20an%20agreed%20way%20of%20handling%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20like%20how%20their%20daughter%20would%20celebrate%20her%20quincea%C3%B1era%20%E2%80%94%20a%20milestone%20birthday%20in%20Mexico%2C%20where%20they%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20who%20are%20considering%20nesting%20with%20an%20ex%20need%20to%20consider%20many%20logistics%2C%20right%20down%20to%20who%20will%20handle%20chores%2C%20buy%20food%20for%20the%20home%2C%20and%20pay%20for%20necessary%20maintenance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENewlin%20said%20she%20and%20her%20ex%20worked%20these%20details%20out%20up%20front.%20They%20both%20stay%20in%20the%20same%20bed%20at%20the%20family%20home%2C%20so%20changing%20the%20sheets%20between%20occupants%20is%20essential.%20At%20first%2C%20the%20person%20departing%20was%20responsible%20for%20changing%20the%20sheets%2C%20but%20they%20later%20found%20it%20worked%20better%20to%20have%20the%20arriving%20parent%20change%20and%20wash%20the%20sheets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20they%20always%20make%20sure%20to%20leave%20each%20other%20with%20grocery%20essentials%20like%20milk%20and%20eggs%2C%20and%20they%20maintain%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-roommates-and-i-share-groceries-to-save-money-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshared%20grocery%20list%3C%2Fa%3E%20via%20an%20app%20called%20To%20Do.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20prevent%20resentment%20between%20the%20partners%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20critical%20for%20nesting%2C%20Scott%20said.%20She%20also%20recommends%20talking%20about%20worst-case%20scenarios%2C%20such%20as%20what%20will%20happen%20if%20the%20nesting%20situation%20is%20no%20longer%20working%20for%20one%20or%20both%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stability%20of%20the%20situation%20lies%20in%20the%20adults%20being%20able%20to%20work%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c7e9726f-2468-4dad-92c1-76638997e674%5C%22%3EIf%20it's%20not%20a%20healthy%20situation%20for%20the%20parents%2C%20it%20won't%20be%20for%20the%20kids%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20choose%20nesting%20to%20benefit%20their%20kids.%20However%2C%20Howell%20said%20it's%20important%20that%20parents%20consider%20their%20own%20mental%20health%20and%20comfort%20level%2C%20since%20that%20often%20impacts%20children%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20much%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famicable-divorce-managing-finances-coparenting-challenges-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_