%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Fsustainable-school-muskaan-ngo-mitti-ka-ghar-7-1751289346-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Fsustainable-school-muskaan-ngo-mitti-ka-ghar-7-1751289346-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Fsustainable-school-muskaan-ngo-mitti-ka-ghar-7-1751289346-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Fsustainable-school-muskaan-ngo-mitti-ka-ghar-7-1751289346-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-458434%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20architects%20are%20also%20restoring%20the%20plinth%20around%20the%20building%20to%20keep%20water%20at%20bay%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20years%20since%20it%20started%2C%20Mitti%20Ka%20Ghar%20has%20braved%20bouts%20of%20unpredictable%20weather%2C%20but%20the%20usage%20of%20Adobe%20bricks%20(sun-dried%20bricks%20made%20from%20a%20mixture%20of%20earth%2C%20water%2C%20and%20a%20binding%20material%20like%20straw)%20in%20areas%20that%20have%20frequent%20water%20exposure%20is%20where%20the%20problem%20lies.%20Architect%20Sourabh%2C%20who%20has%20been%20engaged%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F358205%2Ftiny-farm-fort-homestay-rishikesh-raghav-ansh-kumar-delhi-architects-cob-sustainable-home%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enatural%20building%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20over%20seven%20years%2C%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20bricks%20have%20performed%20well%20in%20other%20areas%20of%20the%20building%2C%20but%20in%20the%20toilet%20area%2C%20because%20of%20constant%20water%20exposure%2C%20their%20structural%20strength%20reduced%20and%20the%20wall%20collapsed.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20moisture%20intake%20is%20compounded%20by%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20black%20cotton%20soil%2C%20which%20tends%20to%20retain%20moisture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESourabh%20and%20his%20team%20are%20now%20attempting%20to%20restore%20the%20fallen%20structure%20using%20red%20brick%20and%20lime%20%E2%80%94%20still%20a%20sustainable%20option%20%E2%80%94%20but%20one%20more%20resistant%20to%20moisture.%20They%20are%20also%20restoring%20the%20plinth%20around%20the%20building%20to%20keep%20water%20at%20bay.%20Architecturally%2C%20this%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20the%20easiest%20process%2C%20architect%20Shaista%20Perveen%2C%20part%20of%20the%20restoration%20team%2C%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20work%20on%20traditional%20structures%2C%20we%20need%20to%20see%20to%20it%20that%20there%20is%20an%20integration%20between%20existing%20traditional%20material%20that%20has%20been%20used.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Fsustainable-school-muskaan-ngo-mitti-ka-ghar-8-1751289440.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20architects%20have%20formulated%20a%20plan%20of%20action%20using%20the%20original%20architectural%20and%20structural%20drawings%20from%20the%20Kamath%20Design%20Studio%20Archives%20to%20help%20understand%20the%20way%20the%20building%20was%20constructed%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Fsustainable-school-muskaan-ngo-mitti-ka-ghar-8-1751289440.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Fsustainable-school-muskaan-ngo-mitti-ka-ghar-8-1751289440-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Fsustainable-school-muskaan-ngo-mitti-ka-ghar-8-1751289440-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Fsus